WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:13.160
I lead our education program at the CIS, which is a great privilege and a great privilege

00:13.160 --> 00:17.040
to be with you all tonight and also to have Konstantin here with us.

00:17.040 --> 00:21.920
Konstantin, I'm very mindful about your safety and the safety of everybody.

00:21.920 --> 00:26.040
So with that in mind, I do want to respect your preferred pronouns.

00:26.040 --> 00:28.400
I understand that.

00:28.400 --> 00:33.280
You do identify as a Bay-Them politically non-binary.

00:33.280 --> 00:35.240
What does that mean?

00:35.240 --> 00:40.080
I think it's very important to think for yourself on everything.

00:40.080 --> 00:47.320
And my experience is that whenever you buy into a political ideology wholesale,

00:47.320 --> 00:50.520
you inevitably end up in positions where you're having to think stupid things

00:50.520 --> 00:52.920
because other people think them.

00:52.920 --> 00:58.160
I don't see that as a healthy way to run your brain, first and foremost.

00:58.160 --> 01:03.480
Now, of course, when your ideas begin to translate into political decisions,

01:03.480 --> 01:06.480
you have a binary choice quite frequently at an election,

01:06.480 --> 01:11.200
although I now understand in this country you have a non-binary system for voting to some extent.

01:11.200 --> 01:16.160
So my primary interest is in trying to understand the world

01:16.160 --> 01:18.560
and get as close to the truth as I possibly can,

01:18.560 --> 01:21.960
which of course all of us are inevitably unsuccessful in.

01:21.960 --> 01:27.960
And therefore, to buy a prepackaged set of ideas just seems to me a little bit naive.

01:27.960 --> 01:32.600
I think left, right, up, down, liberal, conservative, whatever,

01:32.600 --> 01:34.880
they all have flaws in their thinking.

01:34.880 --> 01:38.560
And I'm interested in finding the distinctions and trying to understand,

01:38.560 --> 01:44.480
well, I think, for example, the inequality in our society is a massive problem.

01:44.480 --> 01:46.520
Intergenerational inequality is a massive problem.

01:46.520 --> 01:50.960
And to the extent that the left used to care about that, I agree with the left.

01:50.960 --> 01:55.360
There are also issues that I agree with, you know, conservatives and classical liberals on as well.

01:55.360 --> 02:00.080
So mainly it's about insisting on the ability to think for myself.

02:00.080 --> 02:04.040
And so at the moment, you flag the sort of left, right binary

02:04.040 --> 02:08.400
and the way that you're straddling that, I suppose.

02:08.400 --> 02:11.760
Why is it the left and right labels?

02:11.760 --> 02:14.480
Why do they not mean what they used to mean?

02:14.480 --> 02:19.680
Well, they're both breaking down because what I used to think of as the left,

02:19.680 --> 02:25.760
which I used to be on, due to a combination of ignorance and cowardice,

02:25.760 --> 02:30.240
mostly cowardice, to be honest, have allowed themselves to be derailed

02:30.240 --> 02:33.080
by the people who call themselves progressive.

02:33.080 --> 02:39.040
And my good friend in the UK, Morris Glassman, who's a member of the House of Lords,

02:39.040 --> 02:44.000
he always says this, you know, if you go to the doctor and they say to you, it's progressive.

02:44.000 --> 02:48.800
It's not good news, usually.

02:48.840 --> 02:56.040
So the left has allowed itself to be derailed from its core purpose by the people who are.

02:56.040 --> 03:00.280
And I mean, I mean, absolutely no bones about saying this.

03:00.280 --> 03:05.320
The people who we talk about when we mean the woke left, these are these, you know,

03:05.320 --> 03:10.400
race Marxist or cultural Marxist, these people are the enemy of Western civilization.

03:10.400 --> 03:12.240
There's no discussion. There's no debate.

03:12.240 --> 03:17.520
It's not these people want to destroy the foundations of Western civilization.

03:17.560 --> 03:21.360
That's what they want.

03:21.360 --> 03:26.880
And so if you are the sensible left, which is the majority of people on the left,

03:26.880 --> 03:30.240
and you allow these people to be the tail that wags your dog,

03:30.240 --> 03:33.320
well, then the whole meaning of these words starts to break down.

03:33.320 --> 03:37.520
And by the way, you give ammunition to people on the right who are going to say,

03:37.520 --> 03:38.720
oh, the left are all like this.

03:38.720 --> 03:41.320
Well, if you don't speak up, then that's all happened.

03:41.320 --> 03:44.840
Or if you do speak up as as I found out and many other people find out,

03:44.840 --> 03:46.160
then you become right wing.

03:46.200 --> 03:48.320
So there we go.

03:48.320 --> 03:51.280
So it's well trodden that the the flaws of the left,

03:51.280 --> 03:55.360
when it comes to the aversion around Western civilization,

03:55.360 --> 03:57.840
but the left are on the loan in some of those criticisms.

03:57.840 --> 04:01.200
So just as the left might complain that, you know, big corporations,

04:01.200 --> 04:04.720
for instance, have destroyed society or hollowed it out and so on.

04:04.720 --> 04:09.440
It's also true, is it not that the right have also got this tinge about complaining

04:09.440 --> 04:10.760
about society increasingly?

04:10.760 --> 04:14.360
It's the issues of, I guess, an elite of sorts as well,

04:14.360 --> 04:16.560
that particularly around bureaucracy and so on,

04:16.560 --> 04:20.280
that undermines the true society itself.

04:20.280 --> 04:24.240
But does the right have as much to blame in the current debate?

04:24.240 --> 04:26.440
I see it as a little bit of cause and effect.

04:26.440 --> 04:30.320
I think that many of the policies that progressives have pursued

04:30.320 --> 04:32.080
have created a society.

04:32.080 --> 04:34.320
You're fortunate in this country that you don't have this,

04:34.320 --> 04:37.480
but you only need to travel around major American cities

04:37.480 --> 04:43.120
or come to London to see, I mean, it looks like a zombie apocalypse,

04:43.120 --> 04:43.760
to be honest.

04:43.800 --> 04:46.840
You know, you go to LA, you go to New York, you go to, I mean,

04:46.840 --> 04:50.960
Nashville, anywhere, and there's literally people lying face down on the ground

04:50.960 --> 04:52.640
with most of their clothes off.

04:52.640 --> 04:56.120
And that's because, you know, for all sorts of different reasons,

04:56.120 --> 04:59.680
but primarily because of the policies that governments have pursued.

04:59.680 --> 05:03.600
So as the level of street crime and violent crime increases,

05:03.600 --> 05:06.200
as people see disorder around them,

05:06.200 --> 05:10.400
it's natural for them to get very frustrated about what is happening.

05:10.400 --> 05:11.720
And I agree with you.

05:11.720 --> 05:15.000
I think there is a section of the right, particularly in the United States,

05:15.000 --> 05:22.160
that is so fed up of the inability to vote your way out of this growing nightmare,

05:22.160 --> 05:28.120
frankly, you know, that instead of helping the police to do a better job,

05:28.120 --> 05:30.800
we have these slogans like defund the police.

05:30.800 --> 05:33.640
All of this stuff is causing people to get frustrated.

05:33.640 --> 05:37.080
And then they say, well, look, democracy isn't working.

05:37.080 --> 05:39.200
So maybe Vladimir Putin is brilliant, you know.

05:40.200 --> 05:45.000
Here in Australia, there's been, there's a poll that's done annually,

05:45.000 --> 05:48.000
which asks Australians about their attitudes towards society,

05:48.000 --> 05:49.760
system of government and so on.

05:49.760 --> 05:55.080
And what that's typically shown us is that an increasing number of people,

05:55.080 --> 05:57.840
especially young people, and it's around one in three,

05:57.840 --> 06:02.960
who say that they're unsatisfied with democracy around one in five,

06:02.960 --> 06:07.840
say that they'd prefer an alternative to democracy.

06:07.960 --> 06:11.200
And these numbers, of course, are much higher for young people, especially.

06:12.880 --> 06:17.520
And one of the main reasons that people say that they're not satisfied with democracy

06:17.520 --> 06:20.280
is that they feel that the system no longer works for the majority,

06:20.280 --> 06:21.760
but works for a minority.

06:23.200 --> 06:25.280
Are we all doing democracy wrong?

06:25.280 --> 06:27.560
Well, it's shocking numbers, isn't it, that they're that low?

06:29.920 --> 06:30.560
Well, it is.

06:30.560 --> 06:33.800
I mean, look, the fact is that Western elites,

06:33.800 --> 06:35.680
and I use this phrase advisedly,

06:35.680 --> 06:38.640
have had their heads up their asses for a very long time now,

06:38.640 --> 06:41.040
and they are insistent on maintaining them there,

06:41.040 --> 06:42.920
no matter how many wake-up calls they get.

06:42.920 --> 06:46.680
Look, I voted Remain in the Brexit referendum,

06:46.680 --> 06:51.880
and frankly, if you'd asked me on the morning after why half of my fellow citizens voted from Brexit,

06:51.880 --> 06:54.720
I would have had no idea, right?

06:54.720 --> 06:58.320
But what I took away from that is that I am the ignorant one,

06:58.320 --> 07:00.680
and it's my job to educate myself, right?

07:00.680 --> 07:05.880
What the elites took from that is they need to suppress that movement as quickly as possible.

07:05.880 --> 07:07.280
This was the same with Donald Trump.

07:07.280 --> 07:08.680
Donald Trump gets elected.

07:08.680 --> 07:09.320
What do they do?

07:09.320 --> 07:12.640
Do they say, oh, my God, I can't believe this guy is so obnoxious.

07:12.640 --> 07:17.240
How badly, how desperate must these people be to vote for Donald Trump?

07:17.240 --> 07:17.840
No.

07:17.840 --> 07:19.840
What they do is they go, oh, it's Russia collusions.

07:19.840 --> 07:21.840
The Russians, they said the same with Brexit.

07:21.840 --> 07:25.840
The Russians did Brexit, and I kept saying to these people,

07:25.840 --> 07:29.680
if the Russians didn't vote Brexit, it would be over by now, you know?

07:29.680 --> 07:33.800
We would have taken the chunk of France with us.

07:33.800 --> 07:41.040
So there is this, there is a tyranny of the mind that is happening among people who are comfortable

07:41.040 --> 07:43.360
and who are so attached to the reins of power.

07:43.360 --> 07:47.600
This is why they keep talking, oh, you know, this is a danger to our democracy.

07:47.600 --> 07:51.840
That's why they say our, because it's their democracy, not democracy for anyone else,

07:51.840 --> 07:55.120
because the moment anyone votes in a way they don't like,

07:55.120 --> 07:57.200
they try and overturn it one way or another.

07:57.200 --> 08:01.640
And this makes me sound like some great defender of orange man bad.

08:01.640 --> 08:02.600
I'm not.

08:02.600 --> 08:03.680
I'm just objective.

08:03.680 --> 08:08.400
And objectively, they spent the entire four years trying to undermine the outcome of the election,

08:08.400 --> 08:10.040
lied about him endlessly.

08:10.040 --> 08:12.480
They claimed, and people should go and look at this.

08:12.480 --> 08:16.880
And many people even in our circles still believe this, the idea that he said, for example,

08:16.880 --> 08:19.440
that there are fine people on both sides.

08:19.440 --> 08:20.400
This isn't true.

08:20.400 --> 08:23.120
You can go and watch the video in which he condemns those people.

08:23.120 --> 08:25.120
