09:22.040 --> 09:27.240
And the reason is that they have discredited themselves over a long period of time

09:27.240 --> 09:32.160
by spreading things that later turn out not to be true and driving these narratives.

09:32.160 --> 09:36.920
There's a, I wrote a thread on Twitter that went viral on the subject

09:36.920 --> 09:40.960
that I later made as a video and it's a chapter in my book as well.

09:40.960 --> 09:42.360
It was called Why Don't They Believe Us?

09:42.360 --> 09:46.200
And the reason people are increasingly not believing the mainstream media

09:46.200 --> 09:50.800
is the arrogance with which they have purported these lies

09:50.800 --> 09:53.960
on the publics of the Western countries.

09:53.960 --> 09:58.560
I think what is required is a little bit more humility and admitting wrong.

09:58.560 --> 10:03.480
And I always say this to someone who increasingly has interactions

10:03.480 --> 10:06.080
with people in the mainstream media, giving interviews, et cetera.

10:06.080 --> 10:09.760
No personal, you know, no faith in the mainstream media,

10:09.760 --> 10:12.040
so vice-first contact with the mainstream media.

10:12.040 --> 10:16.600
You know, and an example of this, and I'm not bitter,

10:16.600 --> 10:20.520
but an example of this is after my Oxford speech,

10:20.520 --> 10:23.840
a journalist from the New Statesman came and interviewed me

10:23.840 --> 10:28.120
and he asked me how many views the video of my speech had got.

10:28.120 --> 10:31.520
And I said, it's very difficult to measure because, you know,

10:31.520 --> 10:34.040
it goes into people's telegram groups and WhatsApp groups

10:34.040 --> 10:36.440
and people posting a way that you're not able to track.

10:36.440 --> 10:38.200
So you can't really say.

10:38.200 --> 10:42.000
And he wrote that I'd said that the number of views on the speech

10:42.000 --> 10:43.760
is beyond measure.

