11:05.320 --> 11:07.960
You run a platform like several others

11:07.960 --> 11:11.640
that we broadly define in a family of new media.

11:11.640 --> 11:14.760
And what strikes me is really powerful about new media

11:14.760 --> 11:19.160
is it doesn't have the same opportunity to cancel, if you like,

11:19.160 --> 11:21.680
that mainstream media has. It doesn't have the same conventions.

11:21.680 --> 11:27.000
It provides that free access to masses to be able to access

11:27.000 --> 11:29.040
diverse opinions, diverse perspectives,

11:29.040 --> 11:33.880
and be able to, in many cases, share and disseminate freely.

11:34.720 --> 11:38.200
In some respects, it seems to me this is a set of platforms

11:38.200 --> 11:42.800
that protect against cancellation for those reasons.

11:42.800 --> 11:46.240
And so many more people, when we look at these numbers,

11:46.240 --> 11:49.800
consume new media than consume old media.

11:49.800 --> 11:52.480
Does that mean old media will just die itself out?

11:52.480 --> 11:55.320
We'll see. And by the way, I wouldn't want people to take away

11:55.320 --> 11:59.480
from our conversation that I want the mainstream media to die.

11:59.480 --> 12:03.520
I really, really don't. I want them to be better.

12:03.560 --> 12:07.360
Because one of the problems with new media is

12:07.360 --> 12:11.040
you increasingly see the fragmentation of our reality.

12:11.040 --> 12:15.520
And so I often meet people who have not only alternative opinions,

12:15.520 --> 12:17.840
but alternative facts.

12:17.840 --> 12:21.480
And we no longer can agree on what the facts are.

12:21.480 --> 12:26.160
This is not a healthy place to be. I'd much rather we had

12:26.160 --> 12:28.680
a sort of coherence about what we believe,

12:28.680 --> 12:31.000
but I don't know that we're going to get there.

12:31.000 --> 12:33.840
I think the mainstream media will take some time.

12:33.840 --> 12:38.240
It's kind of bleeding out, but it's still standing.

12:38.240 --> 12:41.800
And that's because there's a lot of people who've grown up

12:41.800 --> 12:45.880
reading and listening and watching the mainstream media.

12:45.880 --> 12:48.200
That will continue. They'll continue to be influential.

12:48.200 --> 12:51.480
And by the way, I keep saying to this,

12:51.480 --> 12:54.040
I am the Turkey that would vote for Christmas.

